text: I’m not a morning person. If you’re a morning person
in this room right now…
hey, if you’re a morning person, congratulations,
good for you.
But I want you to know this fact,
at some point in time in your morning person life,
everybody you know has thought about murdering you.
And not just kind of murdering you,
they’ve thought it all the way through the process.
They’ve drawn out plans, alright?
They’ve put together a list of things
they need to get at Home Depot.
They have gone through the steps in their minds.
So be grateful that they haven’t done it.
Like you know, listen...
you know you’re not a morning person
if you’ve ever done this.
You’re driving your... car 7am, right?
And you see a jogger on the side of the road,
like way too happy to be out of bed.
You know one of those people?
Frolicking down the side of the road
like a happy deer in a Disney movie.
Just pony tail swinging back and forth
with a sassy attitude.
Like, “Hey, look at me everybody!
I’m out of bed on purpose.
I have an E-Trade account.
My life is like a happy musical.”
And you see that person and in your mind you think,
"Wham!"
Right? Like, "Oh, I could've got him,
I could've got him right there."
Elbow goes a little bit…
Ooooh...
I feel better, I feel better right now. Alright?
A little morning person justice right there,
that’s what it was.
You don’t do it, you just think about it in your head.
It makes you feel better.
And I can make it through today because of that.
And relax, morning people,
we wouldn't do it and you’d never die like that anyway.
You’re far too annoying to die like that.
You’d just bounce off the car,
“Ow! Look who’s up early, Mr. Grumpy is.
I love being out of bed!”
You hear that, put your car in reverse and go after them.
"You....vroooom!"
